"""
Smart Probe — H₂ Real-Time Detector  v11
=========================================
ROOT CAUSE FIXED + DELTA-EMF DUAL FEATURE

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
WHAT'S FIXED vs v10
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

1. SLOPE MEASUREMENT FIX (main bug you reported)
   OLD behaviour: max(dvdt) over first 20 samples counted from the moment
   the 5-pt rolling window first crosses the onset threshold.  At that
   moment the 5-pt buffer still contains old baseline diffs → the first
   dvdt reading is UNDER-estimated → triggers onset, then the rolling
   mean keeps rising for ~5 more samples as the buffer fills → ppm
   appears to climb for the first 1.5 s.

   NEW behaviour (MEAN_20 algorithm):
     a) Onset detected (fast or slow path — unchanged).
     b) Wait TRIG_WIN (5) samples so the 5-pt diff buffer is 100% filled
        with transition diffs.  During this delay we do NOT accumulate.
     c) Collect EXACTLY 20 consecutive dvdt values.
     d) slope = MEAN of those 20 values   (not max).
        Mean is more stable across noise.
     e) delta_emf = V[end_of_window] - V[onset]
        (total EMF rise over the measurement window).
   Both slope and delta_emf are frozen at sample 20.  The display_ppm
   is computed once at that moment and NEVER updated until the next event.

2. MINIMUM DIFF GATE
   Your rule: "always require minimum 1 mV interval difference to count,
   except 0→100 ppm where diffs can be 0.5–0.7 mV".
   Implementation: each sample in the 20-pt window is only included
   in the mean if  |diff| >= MIN_DIFF_MV  (default 0.5 mV).  This
   prevents near-flat noise from polluting the slope estimate.
   For 0→100 ppm the diffs are 0.5–0.8 mV so they still pass the 0.5 gate.
   For all higher concentrations the diffs are >> 1 mV so they trivially pass.

3. DELTA-EMF CALIBRATION + DUAL-FEATURE DETECTION
   Calibration now stores (slope, delta_emf) per (baseline, target) pair.
   During detection the hybrid engine uses BOTH features:
     score = w_slope * |slope_meas - slope_cal|/slope_cal
           + w_emf   * |delta_meas - delta_cal |/delta_cal
   The (baseline, target) pair with the lowest combined score wins.
   Weights: w_slope=0.6, w_emf=0.4   (slope has more weight).
   This makes 0→100 ppm detection much more reliable because even if
   the slope estimate is noisy the delta_emf ≈ 4–6 mV is very distinct
   from 0→1000 ppm (delta_emf ≈ 50 mV).

4. CALIBRATION WIZARD: displays BOTH slope AND delta_emf after capture
   and stores both in the knowledge base.

5. CURVES TAB: shows a 2D scatter (slope vs delta_emf per target) in
   addition to the existing 1D slope-vs-ppm plots.

Usage:  python h2_detector_v11.py  [optional_log.log]
Deps:   pip install numpy matplotlib scipy
"""

